description:
CRITICAL CORRECTNESS BUG. The client read path in crates/rift-client/src/view.rs::read (line ~250) computes which chunks to request using fixed 128 KB arithmetic:

    let chunk_size = 128 * 1024u64;
    let start_chunk = (offset / chunk_size) as u32;   // WRONG
    let end_chunk = end.div_ceil(chunk_size) as u32;   // WRONG
    ...
    let start_offset = (offset % chunk_size) as usize; // WRONG

This assumes server FastCDC chunk N starts at byte N × 128 KB. FastCDC produces variable-length chunks, so this is only accidentally correct for single-chunk files (where start_chunk = 0 always). For any multi-chunk file, the client will request the wrong chunk range and extract bytes from the wrong position within those chunks.

The server already provides the correct chunk sizes: drill_result.sizes (Vec<u64>) from merkle_drill at level 1 contains the byte length of each FastCDC chunk in order. This data is received but ignored.

What needs to be done:
1. After receiving drill_result, compute actual chunk byte boundaries from drill_result.sizes:
    let mut chunk_starts: Vec<u64> = Vec::with_capacity(drill_result.sizes.len() + 1);
    let mut acc = 0u64;
    for &sz in &drill_result.sizes { chunk_starts.push(acc); acc += sz; }
    chunk_starts.push(acc); // sentinel = total file size

2. Use chunk_starts to determine start_chunk and end_chunk:
    let start_chunk = chunk_starts.partition_point(|&s| s <= offset).saturating_sub(1) as u32;
    let end_chunk = chunk_starts.partition_point(|&s| s < end) as u32;
    let chunk_count = end_chunk - start_chunk;

3. Fix the byte extraction after receiving chunk data:
    let actual_start_byte = chunk_starts[start_chunk as usize];
    let start_offset = (offset - actual_start_byte) as usize;
    // then slice all_data[start_offset..start_offset + requested_length]

4. Also fix the Manifest stored to cache (line ~290): chunk.index * chunk_size is used as the byte offset but is wrong. Use actual_start_byte for each chunk instead. The ChunkInfo.offset field (crates/rift-client/src/cache/db.rs) should store the correct byte offset from chunk_starts.

5. Add a test: create a file large enough to span multiple FastCDC chunks, read a byte range that starts partway through a non-first chunk, verify correct bytes are returned. Use a MockRemote that returns realistic drill_result.sizes (not all equal to 128 KB).

The merkle_drill call (line ~255) is necessary and correct — keep it. Only the arithmetic derived from its results needs fixing.

Relevant files:
- crates/rift-client/src/view.rs (primary fix)
- crates/rift-client/src/cache/db.rs (ChunkInfo offset field, Manifest storage)
- crates/rift-client/src/cache/ (reconstruct uses stored offsets — verify correctness after fix)
